  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (Minimal Profile)",
  "description": "This package documents credibility evidence for a CFD-based hemolysis prediction model applied to the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump geometry. The model has been applied in clinical research settings to support ventricular assist device (VAD) design decisions, and hemolysis index predictions have informed implant selection criteria in investigational device exemption (IDE) submissions. All thirteen ASME V&V 40 credibility factors have been evaluated under the assumption that the operating envelope and patient population are sufficiently understood from prior peer-reviewed publications. Monte Carlo uncertainty propagation was performed across rheological parameters and rotational speed. The assessment team concluded that the achieved credibility levels, while below the thresholds that would be required at Model Risk Level 5 under a complete COU-anchored assessment, are sufficient for the intended low-risk advisory use within the clinical research programme. Decision: Accepted under Minimal profile scope.",
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/morrison-vad-hemolysis-mrl5",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/morrison-cfd-hemolysis-cou2",
  "bindsModel": "https://uofa.net/synth/model/fda-centrifugal-pump-cfd-v3",
  "bindsDataset": [
    "https://uofa.net/synth/data/fda-pump-piv-experimental-dataset",
    "https://uofa.net/synth/data/morrison-hemolysis-monte-carlo-runs"
  ],
  "hasValidationResult": [
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/morrison-cou2-val-01",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "PIV velocity field comparison — FDA pump 2500 RPM baseline"
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/morrison-cou2-val-02",
